 She'd not been assasinated, but only by the strangest of luck.  Fritz, her old friend, and the man who'd been hired to kill her, was slain on his very way to her.  <br>
But, she'd still had many fights this day, only one of which was physical.  The people who called her &quot;family&quot; had all shown up to watch her be slain.  There were a couple who said otherwise, but the Hate as still there. <br>
 Only Demaste and Syllestrae stood by her side.  Sarhea didn't care one whit whether they liked Shintou, nor did she want their permission to be with him. She had just wanted them to understand that that is how it was.  But they chose not to. <br>
Sarhea heard more Hate...and she remembered it, kept it in a safe place.  They thought they knew best, that she was just &quot;love struck&quot;. That may be, but she was quite aware of the choices she'd made. <br>
<br>
And she would stand with Shintou, ready. Love in her heart, and Hate in her hands.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><center><b><font color="#710672" face="Black Chancery" size="-1">Sarhea</font><font
